<br>
No dropped or purchased pet could replace the epic.  To do so would make MONTHS and YEARS (to some mages) of questing for nothing.<br>
<br>
What I'm more interested in is will these new pets also work in non-PoP zones?  Obviously the pets must be higher than lvl 49, so they'd offer serious power to the old zones.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/upyatthemage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pyat The Mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#333333>(9/26/02 12:07:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=38.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PoP pets</span><hr size=1> Ya, I for one spent a year and 3 months on my epic. <br>
<br>
Would hate to see that go to waste. <p><center><BR><BR><img src="http://www.bloodofro.com/members/gallery_img/finally.jpg"><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=273916">Baron Pyat</a> of The <a href="http://www.bloodofro.com">Blood of Ro</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umourningloree.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mourningloree</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(9/26/02 12:38:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=38.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Will new PoP pets make epic pet obsolete?</span><hr size=1> Look around you and see how many epics are still in use.  See many Main Tanks with light sabers?  Ragebringer gets bagged with Tunare or Ssra.  Clerics are bagging epics except for their effects for items with procs or hps.  Unless there is an overall epic enhancement going on (Which people have claimed is going to occur for each of the last two expansions.)  I believe mages will join the majority of the classes that do not use their Kunark Epic in day to day situations. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=85369">Veteran Mourningloree - Warlord of Rallos Zek</A> <BR>
