<br>
Anyway, comparing our epic to a warrior's/rogues/etc like some people doesnt really make much sense. They are a melee class, they receive better weapons drops from mobs. They bag their epic because of its stats, every class has a better item out there that has better stats than their epic. High end mages bag their epic to hold a better stat item just as rogues and warriors do. Its not the stats though, its the effect. Wizards get a free 900hp rune, Necro's, shamans and druids get a free dot, clerics get a free 96% rez. Those caster classes will always be able to benifit from their epic. If they make dont beef up the mage epic pet to be on a more &quot;PoP&quot; scale then I will really be upset. We will be the ONLY caster class to receive no benifit at all from completing the most difficult epic quest in the game. That makes absolutely no sense to me. If they make PoP summoned pets more powerful than the epic pet then they will be making a huge mistake and I hope you magicians can agree. Stop comparing us to warriors and rogues, we are not a melee class. The stats of the orb we summon is not why we did the quest, or why the wizard did his epic quest. It is for the unique effect they get. <br>
<br>
SZ mage<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucalebe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calebe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 348<br> <font color=#333333>(9/26/02 1:56:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=38.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> One Solution to the Orb Matter</span><hr size=1> IF the new pets are better than the epic pet, make the ORB a focus item for those pets.<br>
<br>
That way, if you do the Epic quest your new PoP pets are better than a non-epic magician.<br>
<br>
Also make the increase from using an Orb noticable, and not just a 2 DPS increase or 1 level. Make it a 2-3 levels and maybe 10-15 DPS more.<br>
<br>
Sure that is a huge gap, about the same an epic mage has now over a non-epic magician.<br>
<br>
Incentive to do the magician epic, but if not you still get a pet as good as the epic or better, just not as good as an epic magician gets.<br>
<br>
Fair and simple idea to make the magician epic valuable, without harming pet upgrades in PoP.<br>
<br>
Thoughts or suggestions both pro and con welcome as always. To me though it sounds like a good idea and easy to impliment.<br>
<br>
Calebe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udmuerte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dmuerte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(9/26/02 5:47:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=38.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: One Solution to the Orb Matter</span><hr size=1> I sure hope that the new pets are better then the 2 year old epic pet. If they are not then whats the point of getting the new pets?<br>
